l flux for over a century suggests that the\nmechanism responsible for their formation is not uniquely manifested by\nenhanced or strongly diminished visual light. The study demonstrates that the\ndusty mass-loss episodes of VY CMa are indeed unparalleled among all known\nnon-explosive stars. The origin of these episodes remains an unsolved problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 22 Mar 2019 15:31:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 May 2019 16:08:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 1 Jul 2019 14:31:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-10"}
